        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "Passing or Failing the Course",
          "Pass ( 0) vs Fail (1)",
          "772 Omani students",
          "1 e-Commerce and a 1 e-Commerce Technologies courses",
          "Academic History, \nLMS logs, \nVideo-Interactions, \nGrades in Course",
          "[CGPA, Attempt Count, High Risk, Term Exceed at Risk, At Risk, Student Success Centre, Other Modules, Plagiarism Count, CW1, CW2, End Semester Examination, Activity on Campus, Activity off Campus, Played, Paused, Likes/Dislikes, Segment]",
          "End of Course",
          "Target is numerical but dsiscretized in order to be usable in classfication.\n\nMost numerical variables, such as GPA were also discretized. Authors used Genetic Algorithms and/or PCA to do feature selection.\n\nComparison is done in terms of binning strategies and feature selection strategies. ",
          "CN2 Rule Inducer, Random Forest, Logistic Regression, Decision Tree, kNN, Naive Bayes, MLP, SVM",
          "10-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "{Accuracy: 0.883 - RF with equal-width binning and IG Feature Selection, Sensitivity: 1: MLPs and RF with GA , Specificity: 1: RF with GA, F1-Score:  0.933 - RF with equal-width binning and IG Feature Selection}",
          "Authors create multiple forms of preprocessing and look to compare how they perform. \n\nEssencially, the gfoal is to use video-watching behavior (eDify) to Predict student performance.",
          "No early prediction - since prediction is done after all materials have been consulted.\n\nAccuracy as primary metric is not ideal in this sort of scenarios,\n\nLMS logs are underexplored as a feature,\n\nSmall sample size.\n\nPreprocessing strategies: the binning, is not a widely explored."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 4
    }
  ],
